      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SEARCH HISTORY (3) flew the lids from the middle with a slick turn of foot before finishing second (17.08) and beaten 1.75 lengths over 300m at this track. Recorded one of the quickest times on the card last start despite being beaten. Good form should continue. LITTLE MASTER (4) started big odds but ran a huge race last time when finishing 3rd over 300m at this track (16.93)in Grade 5. Was a winner this track in lesser company the start prior. Hard to beat again. LARA MOON (1) put in a much better performance last start when in the placings at Warrnambool behind Molly Mckayla (22.62) in a Grade 5. Led around the bend before fighting on well and should give a sight. Still to record a win from this draw but has never missed the frame in two starts. Hard to beat again. FERREL'S LAW (8) boasts a solid strike-rate over this track and distance.",
